v.(使)松弛，放松 【英】 v.(使)松弛，放松(to make less active) 【考】 slacken : tension / blunt : sharpness(使松懈是不再紧张/ 使变钝是不再锋利)slacken : tautness / dilute : strength(放松不紧/稀释不浓)反义词：tauten(绑紧 ) 【记】 和slack(松弛的)＋en 【例】 His business slackens in the winter. v. 使松弛, 使松懈, 使缓和 = loosen = ease 【类】slacken: tension = blunt: sharpness使松懈消除紧张 = 使变钝消除锋利slacken: tautness = dilute: strength放松使不紧 = 稀释使不浓 【反】tauten(v 拉紧) 【记】源自languish 衰弱，无力，凋萎；s + lack，缺少活力，劲头，力量，能量，注意； 【相关】sluggish 行动迟缓的 slacken (v.)  early 15c., from slack (adj.) + -en (1). Related: Slackened; slackening.
